To install the webmin in my local ubuntu server   
**sudo apt update \-y**  
**sudo apt install gnupg2 curl \-y**  
The system has been updated and gnupg package has been installed for encryption.

**cd /tmp**  
**curl \-o setup-repos.sh https://raw.githubusercontent.com/webmin/webmin/master/setup-repos.sh**  
**sh setup-repos.sh**     
      
The setup repo private key has been run and repos get installed from the web.  
**sudo apt update \-y**    ( upto date all device changes )  
**sudo apt install webmin \--install-recommends \-y**   ( this command lets us to install the user and admin panel)  
**Systemctl start webmin** (start the service)

**Sudo ufw allow 22 ( allows connection from port 22 )**  
**Sudo ufw allow 10000 ( webmin runs at port 10000 and allows it from firewall)**
